        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 7 at 5:34PM EDT until July 7 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Grove City,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Law enforcement reported trees down.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines, resulting in some
power outages.

Locations impacted include...
New Castle, Slippery Rock, Oakwood, New Castle Northwest, Bessemer,
Harrisville, Plain Grove Township, South New Castle, West Liberty,
and Harlansburg.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report severe weather by calling 412-262-1988, posting to
the NWS Pittsburgh Facebook page, or using X @NWSPITTSBURGH.</instruction>
